# zStream — host Caddy configuration (TLS front only)
#
# You only need this on a host that already serves OTHER domains (like the
# project VPS), where the system Caddy must multiplex ports 80/443. On a
# dedicated host you don't need it at all — the containerized Caddy provisions
# its own Let's Encrypt certificates (standalone mode; see README).
#
# All zStream routing (app + /live/ + LiveKit) lives in the containerized Caddy
# (stream/caddy/Caddyfile). These host blocks are pure TLS fronts: they
# terminate HTTPS and forward BOTH hostnames to the container's HTTP port
# (:8880). The container then splits app vs LiveKit traffic by Host header.
#
# Replace stream.example.com with your domain, add these blocks to
# /etc/caddy/Caddyfile, and `systemctl reload caddy`. deploy.sh does this
# automatically in behind-host-caddy mode (installs Caddy if missing, appends
# these blocks if absent, never rewrites existing blocks).
#
# Requires .env: SITE_ADDRESS=:80  HTTP_PORT=8880  LK_SITE_ADDRESS=http://lk.<domain>

stream.example.com {
	reverse_proxy localhost:8880
}

lk.stream.example.com {
	reverse_proxy localhost:8880
}
